ues**:\n1. Strength properties (SCT_CD +2.06%, Burst +2.04%) increased beyond necessary levels\n2. Grade 6010100 shows simultaneous cost increase AND overprocessing increase - double penalty\n3. According to [papermaking_science_technology.pdf:d6f6f20ccb65b658:3395:0], "a 1% increase in SCT causes an operating cost increase of EUR 4.73/t" - the observed increases represent significant unnecessary costs\n\n### Grade-Specific Diagnosis\n\n#### Grade 6010085 (Best Cost Performance: -5.74 €/t)\n**Wet End Section** (forming/retention):\n- **Positive**: Consistency white water increased (+0.26), improved retention efficiency\n- **Positive**: Speed increased (+20.23 m/min), better productivity\n- **Negative**: Retention decreased (-0.02%), losing fibers/chemicals\n\n**Press Section**:\n- **Positive**: Vacuum uhle-box Pick-Up increased, better water removal\n- **Negative**: Retention Aid increased (+13.84 g/T), chemical cost penalty\n\n**Drying Section**:\n- **Positive**: DG4 inlet air temperature decreased (-26.80°C), major steam savings\n- **Negative**: Reel moisture decreased (-0.40-0.46%), over-drying\n\n#### Grade 3200115 (Strong Cost Performance: -5.66 €/t)\n**Size Press Section**:\n- **Positive**: Starch uptake increased (+0.18 g/m²), improved efficiency\n\n**Drying Section**:\n- **Positive**: DG4 inlet air temperature decreased (-28.33°C), excellent steam savings\n- **Positive**: Speed increased dramatically (+53.65 m/min), high productivity gain\n\n**Wet End Section**:\n- **Negative**: Retention decreased (-0.02%), fiber loss\n- **Mixed**: Overprocessing at 10.38% indicates excessive strength delivery\n\n#### Grade 6010100 (Problem Grade: +2.37 €/t cost increase)\n**Critical Issues**:\n- **Negative**: Speed decreased (-32.19 m/min), major productivity loss\n- **Negative**: Consistency white water decreased (-0.20), poor retention\n- **Negative**: Starch costs increased (+2.69 €/t), highest among all grades\n- **Negative**: Retention Aid increased (+13.87 g/T), chem